    <h1>Customising the user account</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>On this page, you will find all the information about the settings in plentymarkets that you only have to set up once in order to customise your user account. Of course you can change these settings at any time.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="10">1. Setting the complimentary close</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Go to the <strong>System » Settings » User » Accounts</strong> menu and enter a text in the <strong>My account</strong> area. This text is automatically added as a complimentary close at the end of your messages and comments in the ticket system. Generally, this text consists only of a closing and your name. When sending emails from the ticket system, the complimentary close and the signature will automatically be added to the end of the email. You will find a description of how to set up your signature in the next chapter.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting the complimentary close:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Settings » User » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>My account</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the <strong>Complimentary close</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter your complimentary close.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="20">2. Setting the signature</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Go to the <strong>System » Settings » User » Accounts</strong> menu and enter a text in the <strong>My account</strong> area. This text is automatically added as a signature at the end of your messages and comments in the ticket system. Generally, this text consists of your contact details as well as information about where your company is registered and its registration number. Depending on your company’s legal form, the name of the company, the chief executive officer and, if applicable, the European VAT number are all mandatory entries. When sending emails from the ticket system, the complimentary close and the signature will automatically be added to the end of the email.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Template variable for the signature</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The template variables <strong>$Signature</strong> and <strong>$SignatureHTML</strong> contain the complimentary close.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting the signature:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Settings » User » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>My account</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the <strong>Signature</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter your Signature.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock warning">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-warning" title="Warning"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Mandatory entries in emails</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Since the beginning of 2007, mandatory entries for email signatures in Germany correspond to those for company business letters. Non-compliance can result in a fine or in a costly warning being issued by a competitor.<br>
Read up on the legal regulations for signatures in your own country or contact a legal adviser for such information.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="30">3. Changing personal settings in the My account area</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Go to the <strong>System » Settings » User » Accounts</strong> menu and open the <strong>My account » Personal settings</strong> area to change the settings of the user currently logged into the system. Therefore, you can only see this tab in your own user account. The tab is divided into 3 tabs with settings that only apply to you personally. These tabs are <strong>General</strong>, <strong>Shortcuts</strong> and <strong>Favourites</strong>.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="40">3.1. Changing general settings</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>General</strong> tab you determine whether you want to receive a warning if tabs are open and you try to close the window. You can also reset all user-specific settings.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Changing general settings:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Settings » User » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>My account</strong>.<br>
→ Your account settings open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Personal settings</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>General</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings. Pay attention to the information provided in <a href="#table-general">Table 1</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
