<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Some shortcut combinations are not possible</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Do not use any shortcut that is specific to an operating system. Shortcuts differ from one operating system to the next. For example: the <strong>F</strong> keys.<br>
The combination <strong>cmd / Ctrl + W</strong> is reserved for the browser and is therefore not possible.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting up shortcuts:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Settings » User » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>My account</strong>.<br>
→ Your account settings open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Personal settings</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Shortcuts</strong> tab.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> The <strong>Shortcuts</strong> tab is only visible in your own user account. You are the only person who can edit your shortcuts.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Set the shortcuts. Pay attention to the information given in <a href="#table-shortcuts">Table 2</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
